So, I did a singalongahamish pub gig last night in Worthing. Not much
to do with folk, I suppose, the closest being a couple of Paul Simon
songs. But it was my first since the smoking ban. And, yes, it was
lovely to play in a smokeless atmosphere. But something I hadn't
anticipated was that folks would have to go outside for regular
nicotine fixes. In fact I was on right after the quiz (yes, I know:
but a gig's a gig...) so I started to a half empty pub.

And, observations about how maybe their craving for nicotine might be
increased by my performance aside, I er... thought I'd mention it.

I suppose I should be drawing some lesson or suggesting strategies at
this point, but, er... well, yes, I thought I'd just mention it.

I guess I could say something about always having to be on form, cos
if they go outside and think &quot;I didn't think much of that song&quot; as
they leave, they'll be less likely to hurry back. So don't be tempted
to put any padding in.

...maybe...

...fades out...

--
Hamish
