Not really sure what the effects of the ban in the sessions I go to are
but...

In one the first non smoking night was a very busy and noisy night but
over the last 4-5 weeks. I can not remember a week where I have
struggled for example to hear the Irish pipes the opposite side of the
table to me. I think this has gone with a drop in numbers of drinkers
but not a drop to the extent I would be worrying about our future there.
Maybe it will prove to be some benefit as a result of a law I would
strongly disagree with even if I was a non-smoker - I don't know yet.
The pub has always been variable in terms of numbers, maybe some locals
have been on holiday, etc. but there just may be one change for the better.

I have not been getting to the other one on a weekly basis but numbers
of players have generally been low the weeks I've been.  I think there
are other reasons, eg. holidays, some play in groups, etc for the drop
and not many of that group smoke but the last one did amuse me in some
way. There were only 3 of us and 2 of us were smokers. There was no
music at all when we had our fag breaks.
