Ah yes, I remember the Half Brick. Some years ago we had a session
there, largely for the benefit of TV cameras. A member of the morris
side I played for lived in Ham Road, and the local TV network decided to
do a feature on the people living in Ham road and their various hobbies
and eccentricities. They couldn't believe their luck when they found
that Sally was a morris dancer... Could she arrange for the side to
dance outside her house, maybe tomorrow?

So at about 24 hours' notice we managed to raise a mixed side to do a
processional dance down the middle of Ham Road at the required time,
which was about 5.30 pm, during the evening rush hour. The point of
this, for the cameras, was to demonstrate how Sally and her
morris-dancing friends liked to spend their time dancing down her
street. Passing motorists were (variously) amused, entertained or
exasperated.

We ended up, not surprisingly, in the Half Brick for a bit of a session.
Not one of Worthing's most charming pubs, but yes, quite a roomy pub for
music etc.

I was pleased, when I saw the TV programme with its tantalisingly brief
shots of the morris processsion, that they continued using my music as a
background track to some of what followed (interviews with other people
in the street who kept budgies or collected teapots or whatever).

--
Marjorie
